## The Short Version

mbuzz and HockeyStack solve B2B attribution differently. HockeyStack bundles everything—analytics, surveys, attribution—into one $2,200+/mo platform for teams who want simplicity. mbuzz gives you deeper attribution (8 models + custom rules) at a fraction of the cost, integrating with tools you already have. Neither is universally better—it depends on your budget, team, and what you already use.

## At a Glance

| Factor | mbuzz | HockeyStack |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| Starting price | Free / $29-299/mo | $2,200+/mo |
| Attribution models | 8 + custom rules | 3 (no custom) |
| Tracking method | Server-side (SDKs) | Client-side (script) |
| Web analytics | No (integrate yours) | Bundled |
| Surveys | No | Bundled |
| Setup time | Days | ~2 weeks |
| LinkedIn tracking | Yes | Yes |
| AI assistant | No | Odin AI |
| LTV attribution | Yes | Limited |
| Data ownership | Full export | Platform-dependent |
| Best for | Model flexibility + low cost | All-in-one + fast deployment |

## Where mbuzz Wins

### Price: 7-15x Cheaper

The most obvious difference. mbuzz Pro ($299/mo, 25M records) costs less than HockeyStack's entry point ($2,200+/mo). For bootstrapped B2B companies or those not ready for enterprise pricing, this isn't a minor detail—it's the deciding factor.

| mbuzz Tier | Price | Records |
|------------|-------|---------|
| Free | $0 | <%= free_event_limit_display %> |
| Starter | $29/mo | 1M |
| Growth | $99/mo | 5M |
| Pro | $299/mo | 25M |

vs HockeyStack starting at **$2,200+/mo** and scaling up from there.

### Model Transparency: 8 Models vs 3

HockeyStack gives you 3 attribution models. mbuzz gives you 8 built-in models plus a rule editor to build custom logic. For B2B with 6-month sales cycles, being able to compare how credit shifts between first-touch, Markov Chain, and Shapley Value models is the difference between trusting one view and actually understanding your attribution.

